100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 16, 1926, a significant earthquake struck the town of Aysn in Chile, causing widespread damage and prompting international concern. In political news, French Premier douard Herriot announced plans to stabilize the country's economy amidst ongoing inflation. Meanwhile, in the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to dominate headlines, with calls for reform gaining traction among various political factions.
